triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/public_safety_and_welfare
triples.object: The paramount obligation of engineers to prioritize the safety, health, and welfare of the public above all other considerations in their professional work.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/public_safety_and_welfare/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers must hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public in the performance of their professional duties. This takes precedence over other considerations.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/public_safety_and_welfare/reference/3
triples.object: Never compromise safety standards for cost or schedule

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/public_safety_and_welfare/reference/4
triples.object: Promptly report potential dangers to appropriate authorities

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_competence
triples.object: The obligation for engineers to only perform services in areas where they have adequate expertise, knowledge, and skills.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_competence/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall perform services only in areas of their competence.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_competence/reference/2
triples.object: Maintain and improve technical skills through continuous education

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_competence/reference/3
triples.object: Accept assignments only when qualified by education or experience

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_competence/reference/4
triples.object: Engage qualified experts when projects require knowledge beyond personal expertise

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/truthfulness_in_public_statements
triples.object: The requirement for engineers to be objective, truthful, and comprehensive in all public communications and professional reports.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/truthfulness_in_public_statements/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall issue public statements only in an objective and truthful manner.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/truthfulness_in_public_statements/reference/2
triples.object: Disclose all pertinent information in professional reports, statements, and testimony

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/truthfulness_in_public_statements/reference/3
triples.object: Include all relevant data in public statements

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/truthfulness_in_public_statements/reference/4
triples.object: Avoid statements containing material misrepresentation of fact

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/faithful_agency
triples.object: The duty of engineers to act as faithful agents or trustees for their employers and clients, protecting their interests while maintaining ethical standards.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/faithful_agency/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall act as faithful agents or trustees for each employer or client.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/faithful_agency/reference/4
triples.object: Make employers or clients aware of consequences if professional judgment is overruled

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_integrity
triples.object: The commitment to avoid deceptive acts in professional practice and to maintain honest representation of qualifications and capabilities.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_integrity/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall avoid deceptive acts in the solicitation of professional employment.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_integrity/reference/3
triples.object: Avoid improper solicitation of professional employment

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/professional_integrity/reference/4
triples.object: Base professional reputation on merit of services

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/ethical_conduct
triples.object: The overarching obligation for engineers to conduct themselves honorably, responsibly, ethically, and lawfully in all professional activities.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/ethical_conduct/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall conduct themselves honorably, responsibly, ethically, and lawfully.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/ethical_conduct/reference/2
triples.object: Maintain high standards of honesty and integrity

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/ethical_conduct/reference/3
triples.object: Zero tolerance for bribery, fraud, and corruption

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/ethical_conduct/reference/4
triples.object: Support colleagues who uphold ethical standards

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/sustainability
triples.object: The responsibility of engineers to consider environmental impacts and resource efficiency in their designs and to adhere to principles of sustainable development.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/sustainability/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers should strive to adhere to principles of sustainable development.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/sustainability/reference/2
triples.object: Consider environmental impacts in design decisions

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/sustainability/reference/3
triples.object: Minimize resource consumption and waste generation

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/sustainability/reference/4
triples.object: Design for longevity, reusability, and recyclability

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/intellectual_property_respect
triples.object: The obligation to respect and properly attribute intellectual property rights, including patents, copyrights, and innovations.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/intellectual_property_respect/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall respect intellectual property rights.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/intellectual_property_respect/reference/3
triples.object: Honor patents, copyrights, and other forms of intellectual property

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/intellectual_property_respect/reference/4
triples.object: Maintain proper documentation of design decisions

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/whistleblowing
triples.object: The ethical responsibility to report unethical behavior or practices that could endanger public safety, following appropriate reporting procedures.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/whistleblowing/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers have an ethical responsibility to report unethical behavior or practices that could endanger public safety.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/whistleblowing/reference/2
triples.object: Follow proper reporting procedures within organizations

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/whistleblowing/reference/3
triples.object: If internal reporting fails, consider appropriate external reporting

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/emerging_technology_ethics
triples.object: The responsibility to consider broader societal implications when working with emerging technologies, including potential misuse and impacts on privacy and security.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/emerging_technology_ethics/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers working with emerging technologies should consider broader societal implications.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/emerging_technology_ethics/reference/3
triples.object: Consider impacts on privacy, security, and social well-being

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/emerging_technology_ethics/reference/4
triples.object: Engage with multidisciplinary experts to understand implications

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/cultural_and_global_awareness
triples.object: The obligation to respect cultural differences and consider global impacts of engineering work, including environmental and social consequences.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/cultural_and_global_awareness/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers should be aware of cultural differences and global impacts of their work.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/cultural_and_global_awareness/reference/2
triples.object: Respect local cultural practices and values

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/cultural_and_global_awareness/reference/3
triples.object: Consider global environmental and social impacts

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/cultural_and_global_awareness/reference/4
triples.object: Promote fair labor practices throughout supply chains

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/public
triples.object: The general population whose safety, health, and welfare must be prioritized in engineering work.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/public/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers must hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public in the performance of their professional duties.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/employers_and_clients
triples.object: Organizations or individuals who engage engineering services and for whom engineers must act as faithful agents or trustees.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/employers_and_clients/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall act as faithful agents or trustees for each employer or client.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/colleagues
triples.object: Fellow engineering professionals with whom engineers interact and whom they should support in upholding ethical standards.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/colleagues/reference/1
triples.object: Support colleagues who uphold ethical standards

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/risk_assessment
triples.object: The systematic process of evaluating potential risks and hazards associated with engineering projects to ensure public safety.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/continuous_education
triples.object: The ongoing process of maintaining and improving technical skills and knowledge throughout an engineer's career.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/continuous_education/reference/1
triples.object: Maintain and improve technical skills through continuous education

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/honesty
triples.object: The fundamental value of truthfulness and integrity in all professional communications and actions.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/honesty/reference/1
triples.object: Maintain high standards of honesty and integrity

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/responsibility
triples.object: The value of being accountable for one's professional actions and decisions and their consequences.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/responsibility/reference/1
triples.object: Engineers shall conduct themselves honorably, responsibly, ethically, and lawfully.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/safety_standards
triples.object: Established guidelines and requirements designed to ensure the safety of engineering projects and products.

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/safety_standards/reference/1
triples.object: Never compromise safety standards for cost or schedule

triples.subject: http://proethica.org/guidelines/conflict_of_interest
triples.object: Situations where personal interests could compromise professional judgment or obligations to employers, clients, or the public.
